2.37 pm The Australians converge around Starc, clapping him on and patting him on the back, thankful for his presence for without him they would rarely have picked wickets in this series. Colombo, much like Galle, did not give anything to the fast bowlers but Starc just didn't care. His pace through the air kept him in play all through his 25.1 overs. Starc is the first fast bowler to take three five-fors in a Test series in Sri Lanka

But for all his efforts, Australia are staring at a massive deficit - 355. Their batsmen better have found a way to handle the hosts' three spinners. Not least because they are going one short having dropped Burns and Khawaja

1.05 pm "The weather report says it is going to rain the next three days..Australia may luck out..." Doesn't look like that kind of tour for them though, JackUSA. Already looking brighter overhead. The covers are also being dragged off. Play should resume quite soon.

12.45 pm And it's pouring down in Colombo! The groundstaff were already rushing onto the field while the umpires were getting ready for the next over. They were made to wait, but not a moment later they were vindicated as rain swept over the SSC ground. Barely seconds flick by before the pitch goes under a big blue cover and the square not long after. The flurry of activity, as always, is a spectacle.

There was a fairly dark cloud hovering over the ground as play resumed after lunch, prompting the groundstaff into action but that seems to have gotten a little less angry already. The rain is starting to ease even as more covers are brought on to protect the outfield.
